00:16:02.340 --> 00:16:04.615
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:16:06.440 --> 00:16:09.050
- Are you looking for happiness?

00:16:09.050 --> 00:16:10.172
Who isn't?

00:16:10.172 --> 00:16:13.610
In order to be happy, we
need to feel safe, too.

00:16:13.610 --> 00:16:17.690
But how do we find
peace and happiness?

00:16:17.690 --> 00:16:20.870
Every day, we're flooded by
messages telling us who we are

00:16:20.870 --> 00:16:23.300
and what makes us
secure and happy.

00:16:23.300 --> 00:16:25.010
It sounds a bit like this.

00:16:25.010 --> 00:16:29.250
Happiness equals buying
things and security

00:16:29.250 --> 00:16:32.100
equals punishing crime.

00:16:32.100 --> 00:16:34.350
Let's call this the Old Story.

00:16:34.350 --> 00:16:38.610
It shows a rather uninspiring
picture of human kind,

00:16:38.610 --> 00:16:39.910
but does it work?

00:16:39.910 --> 00:16:42.555
Does buying stuff
actually make us happy?

00:16:42.555 --> 00:16:46.380
Are punishment and revenge
really making us secure?

00:16:46.380 --> 00:16:48.270
The answer is no.

00:16:48.270 --> 00:16:50.950
Studies show that once
people have the basics,

00:16:50.950 --> 00:16:54.480
wealth doesn't add to
happiness, but even reduces it.

00:16:54.480 --> 00:16:58.810
Also, huge incarceration rates
eventually lead to more crime.

00:16:58.810 --> 00:17:01.870
And as a military commander
in Iraq once said,

00:17:01.870 --> 00:17:06.030
we're making terrorists
faster than we can kill them.

00:17:06.030 --> 00:17:08.819
The good news is that,
for the last 30 years,

00:17:08.819 --> 00:17:11.880
science has been telling us
an entirely different and much

00:17:11.880 --> 00:17:13.260
better story.

00:17:13.260 --> 00:17:16.770
For example, our brains
reward us powerfully

00:17:16.770 --> 00:17:19.319
when we do something
selfless for others.

00:17:19.319 --> 00:17:22.500
It gives us a strong sense
of meaning and fulfillment,

00:17:22.500 --> 00:17:25.569
key elements of true happiness.

00:17:25.569 --> 00:17:28.349
In fact, we're
wired for empathy.

00:17:28.349 --> 00:17:31.770
Our mirror neurons respond
sensitively to what others do,

00:17:31.770 --> 00:17:32.880
think, and feel.

00:17:32.880 --> 00:17:35.760
We're more connected to
each other than we think.

00:17:35.760 --> 00:17:39.270
This positive view on
humankind is the New Story.

00:17:39.270 --> 00:17:41.970
And if you listen well,
you can hear it everywhere

00:17:41.970 --> 00:17:43.680
under many names.

00:17:43.680 --> 00:17:46.680
It's the story where ancient
wisdom and modern research

00:17:46.680 --> 00:17:49.320
come together.

00:17:49.320 --> 00:17:52.050
This story says that much
happiness is within us

00:17:52.050 --> 00:17:55.110
after all, so we don't need
to consume our planet trying

00:17:55.110 --> 00:17:57.750
to get it from the outside.

00:17:57.750 --> 00:17:59.670
It also says that
real security doesn't

00:17:59.670 --> 00:18:01.740
come from violence
and punishment,

00:18:01.740 --> 00:18:04.510
but from ensuring that
everyone has what they need,

00:18:04.510 --> 00:18:07.960
including love and respect.

00:18:07.960 --> 00:18:10.330
The New Story isn't
that new at all.

00:18:10.330 --> 00:18:13.090
It looks like the wisest
among us were right all along.

00:18:13.090 --> 00:18:15.550
As Martin Luther King said
in his famous Nobel Prize

00:18:15.550 --> 00:18:16.511
acceptance speech--

00:18:16.511 --> 00:18:17.177
[AUDIO PLAYBACK]

00:18:17.177 --> 00:18:19.052
DR. MARTIN LUTHER KING,
JR.: Man must evolve,

00:18:19.052 --> 00:18:22.750
for all human conflict,
a method which

00:18:22.750 --> 00:18:27.010
rejects revenge,
aggression, and retaliation.

00:18:27.010 --> 00:18:29.527
The foundation of
such a method is love.

00:18:29.527 --> 00:18:30.110
[END PLAYBACK]

00:18:30.110 --> 00:18:31.600
- OK.

00:18:31.600 --> 00:18:35.390
That's all very touching, but
what about crime and violence?

00:18:35.390 --> 00:18:37.250
How do we deal with that?

00:18:37.250 --> 00:18:39.350
Well, in lots of ways.

00:18:39.350 --> 00:18:42.460
For example, have you heard
of restorative justice?

00:18:42.460 --> 00:18:44.530
This method involves
victim, offender,

00:18:44.530 --> 00:18:45.970
and the whole community.

00:18:45.970 --> 00:18:47.950
It's effective,
cheap, and it builds

00:18:47.950 --> 00:18:49.700
community in the process.

00:18:49.700 --> 00:18:52.000
And did you know that
ordinary citizens

00:18:52.000 --> 00:18:54.580
with nonviolence training
are solving conflicts

00:18:54.580 --> 00:18:55.810
all over the world?

00:18:55.810 --> 00:18:59.170
It shows we can do things so
much differently and better

00:18:59.170 --> 00:19:02.260
if we change the narrative.

00:19:02.260 --> 00:19:04.650
The New Story has new heroes.

00:19:04.650 --> 00:19:07.630
Here, we're not consumers,
but contributors.

00:19:07.630 --> 00:19:11.320
What really makes us happy
is finding our unique gifts

00:19:11.320 --> 00:19:13.810
and giving them to the world.

00:19:13.810 --> 00:19:16.760
At the Metta Center, we
believe in the New Story.

00:19:16.760 --> 00:19:19.780
We all have a role to play
in making it come true.

00:19:19.780 --> 00:19:22.760
If you are up to the
task, we can help you.

00:19:22.760 --> 00:19:24.940
Our website offers
lots of free resources

00:19:24.940 --> 00:19:26.605
to help you learn the New Story.

00:19:26.605 --> 00:19:29.612
We've even built a roadmap
to get you started.

00:19:29.612 --> 00:19:31.985
Want to be a part of this story?

00:19:31.985 --> 00:19:32.860
Share it with others.

